Introduction
The global container terminal operator market plays a crucial role in facilitating international trade and supply chain operations. Container terminals serve as key hubs for handling cargo, ensuring efficient movement of goods between different transportation modes such as ships, trucks, and railways. The increasing globalization of trade and advancements in port automation technologies are shaping the future of the market.
