Recent Developments
1.	Technological Advancements: Leading terminal operators are investing in AI-based logistics, predictive analytics, and blockchain-enabled tracking.
2.	Expansion of Port Capacities: Major ports in Asia and the Middle East are undergoing large-scale expansions to accommodate increasing trade volumes.
3.	Sustainability Initiatives: Many operators are adopting electrified cranes, alternative fuels, and carbon-neutral strategies to meet emission targets.
4.	Strategic Mergers and Acquisitions: Companies are forming alliances and acquiring smaller port operators to enhance global reach.
